==English==

===Etymology===
{{ME.}} [[dogge]], from {{OE.}} ''docga'' and Old English noun ''scit(t)e'', verb ''scitan'', from a Common Germanic ancestor.

===Pronunciation===
*(''UK''): /dɒg/, /dQg/ /SIt/
*(''US''): /dɔːg/, /dO:g/ /SIt/

===Noun===
'''[[dog]] [[shit]]''' 

# (''Vulgar'') Fecal matter or solid waste produced by a member of the genus ''[[Canis]]'' (probably descended from the common [[wolf]]) that has been [[domesticated]] by man since prehistoric times.

====Synonyms====
*(''animal''): dog doo, doggie doody, dog poo
* [[puppy puckey]], [[sidewalk apples]], [[poopies]], [[shoe scenters]]

